# fixtures/session-malformed.ttl — a sample session log with a DELIBERATE
# Turtle PARSE error, for the falsifier. The verifier
# `ggen graph validate --files fixtures/session-malformed.ttl` must exit
# NON-ZERO and name this file.
#
# The injected fault is an UNCLOSED IRI on <#event-1>'s prov:used object: the
# urn:blake3: angle-bracket handle below is missing its closing '>'. This is a
# real Turtle syntax error (not merely a SHACL shape violation), which is what
# the current parse-only verifier detects.

@prefix dfl:     <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/dogfood-lifecycle#> .
@prefix prov:    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
